<html>
	<head>
		<title>General Page</title>
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Language" content="en-us">
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=windows-1252">
	</head>
	<body>
		<p><IMG alt="" src="General.jpg"></p>
		<p>This is the General page of the Brainchild configuration program. With it you can 
			change several general settings and options of the Brainchild control. The 
			various settings are explaned below:</p>
		<table border="1" width="100%" cellSpacing="0" cellPadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Text Class name</td>
				<td width="65%">This control is used to change the name of the text class you are 
					editing.&nbsp;
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">File Extentions</td>
				<td width="65%">The extentions of the text files using the text class can be entered 
					here. You must enter the whole extention including the dot. Extentions are 
					seperated by a semicolon. This option is only available when you are not 
					editing the default text class.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Delimiters</td>
				<td width="65%">Here you can enter the delimiter characters. Delimiter characters are 
					those characters which seperate words from each other. Delimiter characters are 
					used by the control in word skipping, word selection and syntax coloring.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Caret style</td>
				<td width="65%">With this control you can change the caret style for the text class. 
					There are three possibilities, Normal, Wide and block.</td>
			</tr>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Column Marker</TD>
				<TD width="65%">When this option is checked you can enter a number in the edit box 
					right of the checkbox which represents the column at which you want the control 
					to render the column marker. The column marker is a vertical line which marks 
					the specific column.</TD>
			</TR>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Automatic bracket matching</td>
				<td width="65%">When this option is turned on the brainchild control will automatically 
					check for a matching bracket each time you type a closing bracket.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Visible error on bracket mismatch</td>
				<td width="65%">This option, when turned on, will show a dialog when the brainchild 
					control could not find a matching opening bracket. When turned of the control 
					beeps the computer speaker when it failed to locate a matching opening bracket. 
					This option is only available when the <i>Automatic bracket matching</i> option 
					is turned on.</td>
			</tr>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Highlight matching brackets</TD>
				<TD width="65%">When checked this option will highlight the bracket next to the caret 
					and it's matching bracket aswell. Opening brackets should be located left of 
					the caret to be highlighted and closing brackets should be located right of the 
					caret to be highlighted.</TD>
			</TR>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Clear trailing spaces</td>
				<td width="65%">When this option is turned on the brainchild control will strip all 
					white spaces from the end of the lines when saving the control contents.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Enable Drag and Drop editing</td>
				<td width="65%">This option, when turned on, will allow you to drag and drop text 
					selections around. The brainchild control will accept drops of text fragments 
					from all other programs which support OLE drag and drop.
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Show selection margin</td>
				<td width="65%">When this option is turned on the brainchild control will show a 
					selection margin. This selection marging can be used to select whole lines 
					using the mouse. It is also used to show bookmarked lines.</td>
			</tr>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Solid selection margin</TD>
				<TD width="65%">When checked the selection margin is not filled with a pattern brush 
					but instead a solid color will be used.</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Show line numbers</TD>
				<TD width="65%">When this option is switched on the control will create a margin on the 
					left side in which the line numbers are displayed. The control will show line 
					numbers upto line 99999. Line numbers larger than that are replaced by -----.</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Fast scrolling</TD>
				<TD width="65%">When selected text scrolling speeds up by scrolling 3 lines up or down 
					instead of just one when you press and hold down the Up or Down key.</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Clear undo buffers after save</TD>
				<TD width="65%">Normally when you have saved the control contents to a file you can 
					still undo the changes made before you the save action. When this option is 
					checked the undo buffers are purged after the control contents is saved.</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Visible whitespaces</TD>
				<TD width="65%">This option will, when checked, show the tabs and white spaces in the 
					text as special characters.</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Case-Fixing</TD>
				<TD width="65%">When this option is turned on the control will fix the casing of the 
					keywords you type. The casing is determined by the way the keyword is written 
					in the <a href="edit_keywords.htm">Keyword Editor.</a></TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Highlight the current line</TD>
				<TD width="65%">This option will highlight the line on which the caret is located by 
					changing it's background color.</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Parse hyperlinks</TD>
				<TD width="65%">
					<P>If this option is turned on the parser will also look for hyperlinks in the text. 
						When it finds hyperlinks it will underline them and you can CTRL+click them to 
						open the hyperlink. There is a fixed list of hyperlinks which the parser will 
						recognize. They are:</P>
					<P><U><FONT color="#0000ff">www. ,&nbsp;http: ,&nbsp;file: ,&nbsp;</FONT></U> <A href="mailto:7">
							<FONT color="#0000ff">mailto:</FONT></A><U><FONT color="#0000ff">&nbsp;,&nbsp;ftp: 
								,&nbsp;https:&nbsp;,&nbsp;gopher: ,&nbsp;nntp: ,&nbsp;</FONT></U>
						<A href="telnet:7"><FONT color="#0000ff">telnet:</FONT></A><U><FONT color="#0000ff">&nbsp;,&nbsp;</FONT></U><A href="news:5"><FONT color="#0000ff">news:</FONT></A></P>
					<P>Note that syntax coloring must be turned on for the byperlinks to work. Hyperlinks 
						will be shown in the configured color except when they are located inside a 
						block of text in which case they will get the color configured for that block.</P>
				</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Show hyperlink tooltips</TD>
				<TD width="65%">This option can be used to turn the tooltips used when hovering over a 
					hyperlink on or off.</TD>
			</TR>
		</table>
		<P>When&nbsp;changing the settings for the default text class you will be presented 
			with a few extra settings. These will only be available when you open the 
			general page for the default text class. The options are as follows:</P>
		<P>
			<TABLE id="Table1" cellSpacing="0" cellPadding="2" width="100%" border="1">
				<TR>
					<TD width="35%">Syntax coloring</TD>
					<TD width="65%">When this option is turned on syntax coloring for all supported text 
						classes is turned on. This is a global option which means that it affects all 
						supported text classes and is only changeable when editing the default text 
						class.</TD>
				</TR>
				<TR>
					<TD width="35%">Undo/Redo hops</TD>
					<TD width="65%">Here you can enter the maximum number of undo/redo hops the control 
						will track. This value must be at least 100. This is a global option which 
						means that it affects all supported text classes and is only changeable when 
						editing the default text class.</TD>
				</TR>
				<TR>
					<TD width="35%">Search History</TD>
					<TD width="65%">Here you can enter the maximum number of search and replace strings are 
						stored in the system registry. The values you can enter here are between 10 and 
						30. This is a global option which means that it affects all supported text 
						classes and is only changeable when editing the default text class.</TD>
				</TR>
			</TABLE>
		</P>
	</body>
</html>
